Wordle Arena Privacy Policy
Effective Date: March 29, 2026

Thank you for choosing Wordle Arena ("we", "us", "our"). We are committed to protecting your personal information and your right to privacy. If you have any questions about this policy or our practices, please contact us.

1. Information We Collect
A. Automatically Collected Technical Information
When you use the app, the following technical data may be automatically collected:

IP address, device type, operating system, and language preferences
App usage statistics and session information
Crash reports and error logs
This information does not directly identify you personally and is used to maintain the security and stability of the application.

B. Account Information
If you sign in with Google, we access:

Your email address and display name associated with your Google profile
If you choose anonymous sign-in, only a system-generated anonymous user ID is stored.

C. Game Data
Your game progress, scores, and statistics
Your friend list and display name (used for multiplayer matching)
2. Device Permissions
Permission	Why It's Needed
Camera	Used exclusively to scan QR codes on the friend-adding screen. No video is recorded, no images are sent to servers. All processing happens locally on your device.
Internet / Network State	Required for multiplayer matchmaking, score synchronization, and Firebase services.
Notifications	Used to deliver game invitations and important updates. You can revoke this permission at any time in your device settings.
3. Third-Party Services We Use
Google Play Services
Used for app distribution and core device services. Privacy Policy →

Firebase Authentication
Manages identity verification, including Google Sign-In and anonymous sign-in. Firebase Privacy Policy →

Cloud Firestore
Stores your game progress, friend list, and in-app data.

Firebase Cloud Functions
Used for secure server-side operations such as matchmaking logic and notification triggers.

Firebase Cloud Messaging (FCM)
Used to deliver push notifications for game invitations and updates. A device-specific FCM Token is generated and stored for this purpose. You can disable notifications at any time in your device settings.

Firebase Crashlytics
Collects anonymous error reports to detect and fix application crashes and bugs. Firebase Privacy Policy →

Google AdMob
Used to display in-app advertisements. AdMob may use advertising identifiers (e.g., Android Advertising ID) to serve personalized ads based on your interests. AdMob Privacy Policy →

Google Play Billing — In-App Purchases
All payment transactions are processed entirely through Google Play's infrastructure. We do not collect, process, or store your credit card or payment details. Google Play Privacy Policy →

4. Sharing & Screenshot Features
You can share your game results or statistics. To do so, the app temporarily generates an image on your device. These images are not uploaded to our servers; they are shared directly through your device's native share sheet.

5. How We Use Your Information
We use the collected information solely for the following purposes:

Account creation and authentication
Multiplayer matchmaking and the friend system
Cross-device synchronization of game progress
Displaying in-app advertisements
Crash and error detection (Crashlytics)
Sending push notifications (game invitations, updates)
Improving our services and performance analysis
6. Data Retention
Your personal data is retained only for as long as necessary for the purposes stated in this policy, unless a longer retention period is required by law. When you delete your account, your data is removed from our systems.

7. Data Security
We implement appropriate technical and administrative measures to protect your data, including Firebase security rules and industry-standard encryption. However, no electronic transmission over the Internet can be guaranteed to be 100% secure.

8. Children's Privacy
Our application is not directed at children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal data from children under 13. If we become aware that such data has been collected, we will delete it immediately.

9. Policy Updates
We may update this policy from time to time. Changes will be posted on this page with an updated "Effective Date." For significant changes, we may also notify you via an in-app notification.

10. Contact Us
For any questions about this privacy policy: sfazlihan@gmail.com
